WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:04.233 --> 00:01:05.751
Sean. Billy. we're here.

3
00:01:19.110 --> 00:01:20.559
Can I shoot a rabbit?

4
00:01:20.594 --> 00:01:21.560
Here.

5
00:01:22.216 --> 00:01:23.217
Go on.

6
00:01:23.252 --> 00:01:25.357
We'll meet you up
at the old barn. alright?

7
00:01:25.392 --> 00:01:26.082
Come on.

8
00:01:36.230 --> 00:01:37.162
It'll be OK.

9
00:02:00.185 --> 00:02:01.531
Hold on there. boys.

10
00:02:08.228 --> 00:02:09.160
Come 'ere.

11
00:02:13.474 --> 00:02:15.649
We were born
into a certain world.

12
00:02:16.857 --> 00:02:18.376
It was chosen for us.

13
00:02:18.410 --> 00:02:19.687
Fated.

14
00:02:19.722 --> 00:02:21.620
Some might think it's brutal.

15
00:02:22.552 --> 00:02:23.829
I say it's glorious.

16
00:02:26.211 --> 00:02:27.764
Now. if you can do
this one thing

17
00:02:27.799 --> 00:02:29.732
you can have all
that it has to offer.

18
00:02:30.698 --> 00:02:31.906
Do you want that. son?

19
00:02:32.804 --> 00:02:33.736
Yeah.

20
00:02:54.998 --> 00:02:56.655
I want you to take
this man's life.

21
00:02:58.899 --> 00:03:00.176
What did he do?

22
00:03:01.004 --> 00:03:02.282
He made a bargain.

23
00:03:03.904 --> 00:03:06.286
Just like you're about to.

24
00:03:06.320 --> 00:03:09.323
Once you enter this world.
you accept that you must kill

25
00:03:09.358 --> 00:03:11.463
or in turn you may be killed.

26
00:03:11.498 --> 00:03:13.914
Once you understand that rule.
it's easy.

27
00:03:15.467 --> 00:03:17.504
You can take a life
without hesitation.

28
00:03:18.781 --> 00:03:20.162
You can build an empire

29
00:03:20.990 --> 00:03:21.887
be a king.

30
00:03:42.667 --> 00:03:44.289
Just breathe.

31
00:04:00.374 --> 00:04:01.962
Please. please...

32
00:04:02.583 --> 00:04:03.619
I'm sorry.

33
00:04:03.653 --> 00:04:05.828
I'm sorry. You don't have
to do this. please!

34
00:04:05.862 --> 00:04:07.381
Don't.
Please. I'm sorry.

35
00:04:08.037 --> 00:04:10.764
I'm sorry. please! Please...

36
00:04:10.798 --> 00:04:11.972
Please...
Finn.

37
00:04:12.904 --> 00:04:14.354
Please. I'm so sorry.

38
00:04:14.733 --> 00:04:15.665
No. no!

39
00:04:16.114 --> 00:04:17.909
No. please!

40
00:04:17.943 --> 00:04:19.876
No. don't. please! Please!

41
00:04:20.498 --> 00:04:21.602
Please!

42
00:04:21.637 --> 00:04:23.328
Just shoot the bucket.

43
00:04:24.018 --> 00:04:25.054
Please!

44
00:04:25.572 --> 00:04:26.573
Please. no!

45
00:04:31.854 --> 00:04:33.373
Sorry! Christ. I'm sorry!

46
00:04:33.890 --> 00:04:36.686
Please. please!

47
00:04:36.721 --> 00:04:38.826
You don't have to do this!
I'm sorry!

48
00:04:39.482 --> 00:04:40.552
I'm sorry!

49
00:04:41.622 --> 00:04:42.830
Please!

50
00:04:42.865 --> 00:04:44.832
Oh. God... Christ!

51
00:06:58.863 --> 00:07:01.072
The fuck is this?

52
00:07:08.838 --> 00:07:09.805
They're fucking empty!

53
00:08:34.890 --> 00:08:36.339
Jack!

54
00:08:36.374 --> 00:08:38.065
Jack. open up!

55
00:09:36.779 --> 00:09:39.299
Psych evaluation.
D.I. Elliot Carter.

56
00:09:39.333 --> 00:09:43.061
In the presence of Dr May.
12th March. 2020.

57
00:09:44.615 --> 00:09:46.133
Have you had any trouble
sleeping?

58
00:09:47.721 --> 00:09:48.342
No.

59
00:09:51.276 --> 00:09:53.037
Any nightmares?
Negative thoughts?

60
00:09:54.832 --> 00:09:55.798
No.

61
00:09:58.939 --> 00:10:00.907
Experiencing a loss of appetite?

62
00:10:02.356 --> 00:10:04.048
No.

63
00:10:04.082 --> 00:10:06.395
He's been undercover
for two years.

64
00:10:06.429 --> 00:10:08.052
He's getting closer
to the violence

65
00:10:08.086 --> 00:10:09.778
but not to any evidence.

66
00:10:10.882 --> 00:10:12.746
This is how UCs get killed.

67
00:10:12.781 --> 00:10:14.299
Feeling aggressive
towards others?

68
00:10:15.162 --> 00:10:16.129
This is different.

69
00:10:16.163 --> 00:10:18.614
It's worse. He's unstable.

70
00:10:20.271 --> 00:10:21.962
Do you think about
your wife Naomi?

71
00:10:24.482 --> 00:10:26.035
How long has it been
since she died?

72
00:10:32.041 --> 00:10:33.111
Two years.

73
00:10:34.319 --> 00:10:35.873
And your son. Samuel...

74
00:10:36.770 --> 00:10:37.737
or was it Sam?

75
00:10:42.914 --> 00:10:43.950
Samuel.

76
00:10:45.227 --> 00:10:46.642
Do you think about Samuel?

77
00:10:50.301 --> 00:10:51.613
Of course I do.

78
00:10:55.030 --> 00:10:56.445
Just let it play out.

79
00:10:56.479 --> 00:10:58.412
See what he comes up with.
That is all I'm asking.

80
00:10:58.447 --> 00:10:59.966
Is he compromised?

81
00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:02.002
Taken any risks we can't explain
to a judge?

82
00:11:02.934 --> 00:11:03.901
No.

83
00:11:07.007 --> 00:11:08.699
He's careful.

84
00:11:08.733 --> 00:11:10.977
We've been here before. Vic.

85
00:11:11.011 --> 00:11:14.187
Years of surveillance wasted
when a UC loses his way.

86
00:11:15.050 --> 00:11:16.396
Let's hope this is different.

87
00:11:33.482 --> 00:11:35.760
You did it. He's keeping you in.

88
00:11:36.312 --> 00:11:37.762
We can do this. Vic.

89
00:11:38.383 --> 00:11:39.730
I've felt the shift.

90
00:11:40.800 --> 00:11:42.871
We know Sean threw a boy
off a building.

91
00:11:42.905 --> 00:11:44.735
And may he rest in peace
but if it doesn't connect

92
00:11:44.769 --> 00:11:48.083
to the shell companies.
or the asset funds

93
00:11:48.117 --> 00:11:50.119
it doesn't touch the Wallace
organisation.

94
00:11:50.154 --> 00:11:52.812
We know they launder through
their property empire. hmm?

95
00:11:54.089 --> 00:11:56.401
Sean is overseeing all that now.

96
00:11:56.436 --> 00:11:57.886
He's not just building
the towers.

97
00:11:57.920 --> 00:11:58.956
Then we'll need a paper trail.

98
00:12:00.751 --> 00:12:01.993
Alex?
Dumani?

99
00:12:02.028 --> 00:12:03.719
He pushes the numbers.

100
00:12:03.754 --> 00:12:05.514
Keeps his nose clean.
Steers clear of the bodies.

101
00:12:05.548 --> 00:12:06.929
And that's helpful to us how?

102
00:12:06.964 --> 00:12:08.448
There's no way he can stay clean

103
00:12:08.482 --> 00:12:10.070
while Sean's running it.

104
00:12:10.105 --> 00:12:12.003
And if we're lucky.
this will get messy.

105
00:12:12.038 --> 00:12:13.108
Lucky?

106
00:12:14.212 --> 00:12:15.731
For whom?

107
00:12:26.155 --> 00:12:27.191
Yes. Mr Wallace.

108
00:12:45.865 --> 00:12:47.280
Fucking 'ell. Jack.

109
00:12:53.355 --> 00:12:54.805
What does it look like to you?

110
00:13:03.192 --> 00:13:04.849
I mean. I dunno.

111
00:13:06.886 --> 00:13:09.474
A man doesn't fight for his life
then kill himself.

112
00:13:11.166 --> 00:13:13.202
You're the only one he told
about the Traveller kid.

113
00:13:15.239 --> 00:13:17.137
Lot of havoc being done
on your word.

114
00:14:07.567 --> 00:14:08.948
...has done nothing

115
00:14:08.982 --> 00:14:10.881
to quell the rise
in foreign investors

116
00:14:10.915 --> 00:14:12.434
pushing up our property prices.

117
00:15:09.249 --> 00:15:13.012
Should I become
the Mayor of London

118
00:15:13.046 --> 00:15:16.291
I am committed to ending
this cycle of addiction

119
00:15:16.325 --> 00:15:17.948
and violence on the streets.

120
00:15:17.982 --> 00:15:21.054
I will be demanding more police.
more care

121
00:15:21.089 --> 00:15:22.159
in our communities...

122
00:15:27.612 --> 00:15:30.650
And I want people to stop
looking at them

123
00:15:30.684 --> 00:15:32.652
as potential extremists
and to start

124
00:15:32.686 --> 00:15:35.310
seeing them as leaders of men.

125
00:16:37.820 --> 00:16:40.306
They got to Jack.
Slit his wrists.

126
00:16:40.823 --> 00:16:41.963
Fuck.

127
00:16:43.792 --> 00:16:46.070
Whoever killed Finn.
they're tidying up.

128
00:16:47.071 --> 00:16:48.417
That's what it looks like.

129
00:16:49.522 --> 00:16:50.972
So what do we know
about the car?

130
00:16:52.076 --> 00:16:54.561
The number plates belong
to Patrick Day.

131
00:16:54.596 --> 00:16:56.184
Who?
One of Kinney's crew.

132
00:16:56.218 --> 00:16:57.185
Where is he now?

133
00:16:57.219 --> 00:17:00.257
Gone. Car dumped outside
a warehouse. south.

134
00:17:00.291 --> 00:17:01.154
Three bodies inside.

135
00:17:04.778 --> 00:17:06.056
We're on the Kinney thing.
right?

136
00:17:06.090 --> 00:17:08.265
We've got uniform shaking down
sites now.

137
00:17:10.232 --> 00:17:11.337
Always a step ahead.

138
00:17:14.305 --> 00:17:15.582
How you holding up?

139
00:17:17.757 --> 00:17:19.276
What's Asif doing here?

140
00:17:21.209 --> 00:17:23.073
Listen. As your partner.
I made a call.

141
00:17:23.556 --> 00:17:24.833
We let Asif trade.

142
00:17:26.731 --> 00:17:28.078
We need him.

143
00:17:29.527 --> 00:17:31.184
My cows.

144
00:17:31.219 --> 00:17:32.392
Thirty years...

145
00:17:33.186 --> 00:17:34.532
we've never had a problem.

146
00:17:34.567 --> 00:17:37.777
Thirty years and you
didn't even come to the funeral.

147
00:17:37.811 --> 00:17:39.054
I sent my son.

148
00:17:40.676 --> 00:17:42.575
My flesh and blood.

149
00:17:42.609 --> 00:17:45.095
Asif. you know your business
is important to us.

150
00:17:46.441 --> 00:17:47.821
We are in...

151
00:17:48.477 --> 00:17:50.065
an adjustment period.

152
00:17:51.584 --> 00:17:53.275
Sean is running things now.

153
00:17:54.621 --> 00:17:55.795
It's what Finn wanted.

154
00:18:07.427 --> 00:18:10.361
My deepest condolences
for your loss.

155
00:18:10.396 --> 00:18:13.502
Finn was a great man.
an excellent business partner.

156
00:18:14.331 --> 00:18:16.333
We know who the shooter was.

157
00:18:16.367 --> 00:18:18.438
A Traveller kid.
My men are looking.

158
00:18:18.473 --> 00:18:19.784
You've got trouble
with these people?

159
00:18:19.819 --> 00:18:21.338
Nothing to warrant killing him.

160
00:18:22.960 --> 00:18:24.099
That's not good.

161
00:18:24.651 --> 00:18:25.894
A man of Finn's standing

162
00:18:25.928 --> 00:18:28.690
should not be that easy
to take out.

163
00:18:28.724 --> 00:18:30.140
Your organisation is weak
somewhere.

164
00:18:31.486 --> 00:18:32.487
What are you saying?

165
00:18:32.521 --> 00:18:34.213
First they come for you

166
00:18:34.247 --> 00:18:36.732
now someone has got to
your business partner. Me.

167
00:18:38.596 --> 00:18:40.564
My shipment was hit yesterday.

168
00:18:40.598 --> 00:18:42.324
I gave an order that no one
moves any dope

169
00:18:42.359 --> 00:18:43.739
until I find the killer.

170
00:18:43.774 --> 00:18:45.327
It obviously didn't reach you.

171
00:18:45.362 --> 00:18:48.123
If you impose an embargo.
you will start a war.

172
00:18:48.158 --> 00:18:51.678
A war was started
when my father was shot.

173
00:18:57.546 --> 00:18:59.548
You've got his temper.

174
00:19:00.929 --> 00:19:03.173
Believe me. if they were to
kill my son...

175
00:19:04.691 --> 00:19:07.108
I would wipe out
their bloodline.

176
00:19:08.937 --> 00:19:11.250
But I would not lose a Rupee
in the act.

177
00:19:14.874 --> 00:19:16.186
Be smart. Sean.

178
00:19:19.396 --> 00:19:21.432
Anyone not helping find
Dad's killer

179
00:19:22.606 --> 00:19:24.194
looks suspect to me.

180
00:19:25.022 --> 00:19:27.128
He always said you wanted
a piece of London.

181
00:19:27.921 --> 00:19:29.682
Now your son's running
for mayor.

182
00:19:31.270 --> 00:19:34.514
Without our support.
it might be difficult for Nasir.

183
00:19:42.315 --> 00:19:43.420
Sean...

184
00:19:46.457 --> 00:19:48.942
I'm down five million pounds.

185
00:19:50.806 --> 00:19:52.187
What is bad for me...

186
00:19:53.015 --> 00:19:54.362
is bad for you.

187
00:20:04.268 --> 00:20:06.581
This is shaming us as a family.

188
00:20:06.615 --> 00:20:08.479
There was a time when nobody
would've dared

189
00:20:08.514 --> 00:20:09.791
touch Finn Wallace.

190
00:20:09.825 --> 00:20:10.964
They got lucky.

191
00:20:12.656 --> 00:20:14.175
Why was he even in that flat?

192
00:20:17.005 --> 00:20:18.593
We have to be honest
with ourselves.

193
00:20:21.906 --> 00:20:23.253
What if it was personal?

194
00:20:24.392 --> 00:20:25.910
Some woman's husband.

195
00:20:25.945 --> 00:20:28.534
We're not picking the flesh
off a dead man's bones.

196
00:20:28.568 --> 00:20:29.466
We have to.

197
00:20:31.364 --> 00:20:33.884
♪ I wouldn't hesitate

198
00:20:35.713 --> 00:20:36.956
How did it go with Asif?

199
00:20:38.647 --> 00:20:39.993
He's taken a hit.

200
00:20:40.028 --> 00:20:42.927
A missing shipment isn't good
for any of us.

201
00:20:42.962 --> 00:20:44.722
If there's anyone dealing smack
in London

202
00:20:44.757 --> 00:20:45.999
I want to know about it.

203
00:20:48.968 --> 00:20:50.003
What can I do?

204
00:20:51.281 --> 00:20:52.040
Nothing.

205
00:20:59.427 --> 00:21:02.982
♪ Love is not a toy

206
00:21:03.016 --> 00:21:06.019
♪ When you find the one
you love ♪

207
00:21:06.054 --> 00:21:08.746
♪ She'll fill your heart
with joy... ♪

208
00:21:08.781 --> 00:21:10.610
I'm gonna make
things right. Mum.

209
00:21:10.645 --> 00:21:12.854
♪ If we could start anew...

210
00:21:12.888 --> 00:21:14.407
I know you will.

211
00:21:14.442 --> 00:21:16.547
♪ I wouldn't hesitate

212
00:21:17.755 --> 00:21:19.723
I'm proud of you both.

213
00:21:21.138 --> 00:21:25.280
Billy's clean.
and you're strong.

214
00:21:27.386 --> 00:21:29.905
♪ Pain in my heart

215
00:21:29.940 --> 00:21:32.287
If it was a woman.
she didn't love my husband.

216
00:21:34.565 --> 00:21:36.740
If she had...

217
00:21:36.774 --> 00:21:38.983
she wouldn't have
had him shot in the face.

218
00:21:40.053 --> 00:21:41.434
♪ Oh. oh

219
00:21:41.469 --> 00:21:43.919
♪ You...

220
00:23:25.124 --> 00:23:26.677
Good to see you. Ed.

221
00:23:26.712 --> 00:23:28.921
And yourself.
Nice place to meet.

222
00:23:28.955 --> 00:23:31.130
Next week.
it's my daughter's birthday.

223
00:23:31.164 --> 00:23:32.200
Ah.

224
00:23:34.754 --> 00:23:35.997
How is Sean?

225
00:23:36.031 --> 00:23:37.723
He doesn't know
who he can trust.

226
00:23:38.206 --> 00:23:39.414
Yourself included.

227
00:23:40.898 --> 00:23:42.900
Come on. Ed.

228
00:23:42.935 --> 00:23:46.179
You're not that stupid
to think I pulled the trigger.

229
00:23:46.214 --> 00:23:48.941
I have no idea what Finn was
even doing there that night.

230
00:23:49.942 --> 00:23:52.013
I shook hands with Finn
on the deal.

231
00:23:53.083 --> 00:23:54.187
A Luan deal.

232
00:23:58.882 --> 00:24:00.055
That's my part completed.

233
00:24:00.746 --> 00:24:02.575
In full.

234
00:24:02.610 --> 00:24:06.130
And now the Wallace organisation
has to honour Finn's part.

235
00:24:09.686 --> 00:24:12.930
The Wallace organisation
will do what is right for us.

236
00:24:15.277 --> 00:24:16.796
Of course. I can go to Sean.

237
00:24:18.729 --> 00:24:20.731
Eddie...

238
00:24:20.766 --> 00:24:23.631
they saying you are the keeper
of Finn's secrets.

239
00:24:25.080 --> 00:24:26.599
But you didn't know
about this one.

240
00:25:50.124 --> 00:25:52.264
Move.

241
00:25:56.130 --> 00:25:57.787
Keep coming.

242
00:26:00.099 --> 00:26:00.997
Stop!

243
00:26:01.963 --> 00:26:03.171
Spread them out.

244
00:26:18.946 --> 00:26:20.672
Good evening. gentlemen.

245
00:26:22.881 --> 00:26:23.951
Welcome to the UK.

246
00:26:26.609 --> 00:26:29.853
You are all links in the chain
of my operation.

247
00:26:29.888 --> 00:26:33.823
One of you is responsible
for my cargo being hit.

248
00:27:09.790 --> 00:27:10.618
I...

249
00:27:45.135 --> 00:27:46.378
Room service!

250
00:29:14.293 --> 00:29:15.363
Nick.

251
00:29:15.950 --> 00:29:16.710
Nick!

252
00:29:17.262 --> 00:29:18.919
Where did you get this?

253
00:29:18.953 --> 00:29:20.023
Where did you get it from?

254
00:29:20.852 --> 00:29:21.922
Who's dealing?

255
00:29:22.405 --> 00:29:23.578
Nick!

256
00:29:23.613 --> 00:29:24.510
Fuck...

257
00:29:39.871 --> 00:29:41.527
Well. we've had every
Traveller site

258
00:29:41.562 --> 00:29:43.253
in the southwest turned over.

259
00:29:43.288 --> 00:29:45.186
No sign of Kinney
and no answers.

260
00:29:46.360 --> 00:29:48.017
Our boys have put word out
on the street.

261
00:29:52.642 --> 00:29:55.576
He should be outside.
Elliot stays where he is.

262
00:29:55.610 --> 00:29:57.233
He's the only one bringing me
answers right now.

263
00:29:58.510 --> 00:30:01.064
Why did you tell Asif
to keep dealing?

264
00:30:01.099 --> 00:30:04.274
I told you that was my decision.
Not Dad's.

265
00:30:04.309 --> 00:30:06.518
You should have consulted me.
You were burying Finn.

266
00:30:07.899 --> 00:30:09.832
We need money
and we trust the Afridis.

267
00:30:09.866 --> 00:30:10.902
I don't.

268
00:30:23.535 --> 00:30:24.398
Sean.

269
00:30:58.881 --> 00:31:01.573
My son was hired
by someone to kill your father.

270
00:31:05.888 --> 00:31:07.510
You're saving his skin.
Yeah.

271
00:31:09.374 --> 00:31:10.616
But I'm telling the truth.

272
